Lab- Assignment 1 CLO-5 Marks [10]
You have just been hired as a Junior Linux System Administrator at a company called TechNova Solutions. On your
first day, your manager gives you access to an Ubuntu server and asks you to perform several administrative and file
management tasks to verify your Linux skills. You are currently logged into the system.
Task 1: System Information Check
1. Display the current calendar.
2. Display the current date and time.
3. Show your present working directory.
4. Display system memory usage.
5. Display disk usage in human-readable format.
6. List all files (including hidden files) in the current directory using all possible listing options.
Task 2: Directory Structure Setup
1. 2. 3. Create the directory structure in a single command where possible.
Navigate to the technova directory using a full path.
Navigate to the reports directory using a relative path.
4. Confirm your current location.
Task 3: File Creation and Editing
1. 2. 3. 4. Create three empty files inside reports:
a. report1.txt
b. report2.txt
c. summary.txt
Open report1.txt using a text editor
Append the current date to report1.txt using a command (without opening the editor).
Display the contents of report1.txt
Task 4: Copying and Backup
1. 2. 3. Copy report1.txt to the backup directory.
Rename the copied file to report1_backup.txt during the copy process.
List the contents of the backup directory to confirm.
Task 5: File and Directory Removal
1. Delete report2.txt.
2. Remove the summary.txt file.
3. Attempt to remove the logs directory (observe what happens).
4. Remove the logs directory properly.
5. Remove the entire backup directory.
